tool.name: ProcessLISST

param.name: in_boundary
param.dialogReference: The input boundary to which the GA LISST data will be processed to. The boundary must be a shapefile or feature class polygon.

param.name: output_folder
param.dialogReference: Optionally, provide a folder where the output layers will be saved to. By default, the tool saves the output layers to a folder called "ga_lisst_layers" within the project's home folder.

tool.summary:
Author: Colin T. Stiles, GISP

Last Edited Date: 2025-05-01

Description: This tool is the only tool within the KH GA LISST toolbox.

GA LISST is the acronym for the Georgia Low Impact for Solar Siting Tool. More information for the LISST can be found here (https://www.nature.org/en-us/about-us/where-we-work/united-states/georgia/stories-in-georgia/low-impact-solar-renewable-energy/?vu=georgiasolar).

This script is designed to retrieve the GA LISST data from the REST, convert the raster data into a polygon layer, clip the dataset to within a project's boundary, and calculate acreages for each of the LISST's ranks.

The ranks defined by the LISST are as follows:

  • "Most preferred for low impact"

  • "Less preferred for low impact"

  • "Not preferred for low impact"

  • "Avoidance recommended"

Args:

  • in_boundary (GPFeatureLayer): Input feature layer or shapefile representing the project boundary. Must be a polygon.

  • output_folder (DEFolder, optional): Path to the folder where output files will be saved. If not provided, a folder named "ga_lisst_layers" will be created in the project's home folder. Defaults to None.

Returns:

  • GPFeatureLayer: The output polygon feature layer with acreage calculations for each LISST rank.
